This last fact is a little subtle.
 Naively, we could just write the Taylor expansion 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi(x)=\phi(0)+\phi'(0)\epsilon+O(\epsilon^{2})$
\end_inset

 to obtain 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi(\epsilon)-\phi(-\epsilon)=2\phi'(0)\epsilon+O(\epsilon^{2}).$
\end_inset

 However, it turns out that test functions 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi(x)$
\end_inset

 are not analytic (do not have a convergent Taylor series) at all
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

.
 Nevertheless, because 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 is differentiable with bounded 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi'$
\end_inset

, it follows that 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi(x)$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Lipshitz continuous:
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $|\phi(x)-\phi(y)|<K|x-y|$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $x,y$
\end_inset

 and for some constant 
\begin_inset Formula $K>0$
\end_inset

 (e.g.
 you can prove this from the mean-value theorem of analysis), so 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi(\epsilon)-\phi(-\epsilon)<2K\epsilon$
\end_inset

 and the result follows.
 But I don't expect you to provide this level of proof; a Taylor argument
 is acceptable.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Use 
\begin_inset Formula $f'\{\phi\}=f\{-\phi'\}=f\{-[\phi-\phi(0)]'\}=f'\{\phi-\phi(0)\}$
\end_inset

.
 Then substitute 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi-\phi(0)$
\end_inset

 into the previous part, and note that since the integrand 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\phi(x)-\phi(0)}{x}$
\end_inset

 is now finite as 
\begin_inset Formula $x\to0$
\end_inset

 [since 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi(x)-\phi(0)$
\end_inset

 goes to zero as 
\begin_inset Formula $x\to0$
\end_inset

, at least proportionally to 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 or faster as in the previous part], we can now just take the limit to write
 
\begin_inset Formula $f'\{\phi\}=\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}g(x)[\phi(x)-\phi(0)]dx$
\end_inset

 without using the CPV.
\end_layout

